news.title: UltraTech Cement to acquire Wonder Cement's subsidiary for ₹235 crore
news.para: UltraTech Cement has executed a share purchase agreement with the existing shareholders of Wonder WallCare.

news.title: Dhruv Agarwala to step down as REA India's CEO
news.para: Dhruv Agarwala will remain with the business to support the appointment of his successor and ensure a leadership transition before departing. A comprehensive process to appoint a new CEO is underway.

news.title: Pinjore: 13 years on, 24 houses for poor remain unallotted
news.para: These vacant 411-sq ft houses, accompanied with a community centre, park, and temple, have in fact started to crumble. Over these years, govt after govt passed, but the facility, which could have been utilised by the homeless, continues to lie unused.

news.title: Delhi: Signature View Apartment residents protest as DDA delays promised rent on flat vacating
news.para: "Despite vacating their homes long ago, owners of 111 flats are yet to receive the agreed-upon rent, as the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has failed to take possession of the properties," Amrinder Singh Rakesh, president of Signature View Apartment RWA said.

news.title: Mumbai: New India Cooperative Bank's ex-chairman, wife now proclaimed offenders
news.para: The same magistrate's court has also allowed the police to attach 21 properties, including a Rs 150-crore Slum Rehabilitation Project, worth Rs 167.85 crore of five accused in the case, marking the first such action in the city after the new criminal laws came into force.

news.title: Toronto home sales fall  2.4% in March amid trade uncertainty: TRREB data
news.para: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Wednesday that he would impose a 10% baseline tariff on all imports to the United States, deepening a trade war that could upend Canada's economy.

news.title: Dusit International to expand its presence in India with 10 more hotels
news.para: The company has inked three key properties in Karnataka, which include the wellness-focused Devarana Sakleshpur, set to open in 2028, and two upcoming Dusit Princess Hotels & Resorts.

news.title: RealPage sues California city officials over rental algorithm ban
news.para: Texas-based RealPage said Berkeley's ordinance, which goes into effect this month violates the company's free speech rights and is the result of an "intentional campaign of misinformation and often-repeated false claims" about its products.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body achieves Rs 150 crore property tax target
news.para: Despite senior deputy mayor Rakesh Prashar's repeated requests for the state govt to release the remaining share of the goods and services tax (GST), the funds have not been disbursed.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body collects Rs 800 crore property tax in FY25
news.para: Navi Mumbai: Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation (NMMC) has collected more than Rs 800 crore in property tax for the first time since it was established 30 years ago.

news.title: India’s office space leasing rises 74% to record 282 lakh sq ft in Q4 FY25: Knight Frank
news.para: Among eight major cities, Knight Frank data showed that the gross leasing of office space in Bengaluru jumped more than three times to 127 lakh square feet during January-March 2025 from 35 lakh square feet in the year-ago period.

news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA collects record Rs 1,599 crore revenue in FY 2024-25
news.para: The authority "repaid loans and there is no liability", a senior official said, adding that during the last 10 years, GDA's coffers were never so full and this will give impetus to development projects.

news.title: Housing sales in India rise 2 % to 88,274 units across eight cities in Q4 FY25: Knight Frank
news.para: During January-March, the consultant said that primary residential sales reached 88,274 units, a 2 per cent annual increase over the year-ago period.

news.title: Institutional investments in India surge 31% to $1.3 billion in Q4 FY25: Colliers
news.para: "With USD 0.8 billion inflows, domestic investments saw a 75 per cent annual rise and were largely focused on industrial & warehousing and office segments," it said.

news.title: Contractor penalized for delays in TNUHDB projects in Chennai
news.para: The 118.53 crore project at Andimaniyam Thottam, ward 126, Mandavelli, aims to deliver 702 residential units using pre-fabricated concrete technology within 18 months.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body offers two-month rebate scheme for property taxpayers
news.para: The municipal corporation has scheduled the rebate period from April 1 to May 31, though the official notification is pending. The tax rates have been hiked for the first time since 2020.

news.title: Shree Cement commissions 3 MTPA grinding unit in Etah
news.para: The strategic location of the unit, close to railway infrastructure, enables cost-effective transportation of raw materials from Rajasthan, while cement dispatch will leverage both roadways and railways, it added.

news.title: Telangana HC halts work on 400-acre land in Hyderabad till Apr 3
news.para: The ministry also directed the additional chief secretary (forests), Telangana, to take legal action under forest and wildlife laws as applicable.

news.title: Karnataka HC allows ED to investigate MUDA land allotment case
news.para: The ED had approached the division bench seeking a stay on a single-judge bench order that had quashed the summons issued to Natesh.

news.title: Residents of Signature View Apartments in Delhi to stage protest on April 3
news.para: ​​​The residents alleged that the officials failed to comply with both the lieutenant governor's directive and Delhi High Court's ruling, which declared the building unsafe for habitation and mandated DDA to provide immediate rental compensation.
